Package net.emuman.spigotutils.menu

Class MenuPage

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.emuman.spigotutils.menu.MenuPage
  • public class MenuPage
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing a page in a given menu, can contain numerous buttons.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MenuPage

        public MenuPage​(BasicMenu menu,
                int rows,
                java.lang.String title)
        Creates a new MenuPage.
        Parameters:
        menu - the menu that this page belongs to.
        rows - the number of rows in this page (must be between 1 and 6, both inclusive).
        title - the display title of this menu page.

    • Method Detail

      • addButton

        public void addButton​(MenuButton button,
                      int x,
                      int y)
        Adds a button to the menu page. Can be used to overwrite existing buttons. Coordinates start at the top left.
        Parameters:
        button - the button to add to the page.
        x - the x-coordinate of the button, starting from 0.
        y - the y-coordinate of the button, starting from 0.

      • nextPage

        public MenuPage nextPage​(boolean wrap)
        Returns the page after this one. If wrap is set to true, the last page will point to the first. Else, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        wrap - whether or not to wrap the output.
        Returns:
        the next page.

      • previousPage

        public MenuPage previousPage​(boolean wrap)
        Returns the page before this one. If wrap is set to true, the first page will point to the last. Else, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        wrap - whether or not to wrap the output.
        Returns:
        the next page.

      • onClick

        public void onClick​(org.bukkit.event.inventory.InventoryClickEvent event)
        Called by the menu when an inventory is clicked. Should generally not be called by user.
        Parameters:
        event - the InventoryClickEvent associated with the click.

      • getInv

        public org.bukkit.inventory.Inventory getInv()
        This is the call that should be made when opening the menu page for a given player (Player#openInventory(MenuPage#getInv)).
        Returns:
        the Inventory that this page wraps around.
